{"id": 3033, "source": "pestle", "subject": "physics", "course": null, "level": "HL", "paper": "1", "year": "2022", "session": "22M", "subtopic": "11-3-capacitance", "title": "22M.1.HL.TZ1.37", "topic_id": "11", "source_url": "https://pestle.pages.dev/app/", "question_html": "<div class=\"question\">\n<p>Three identical capacitors are connected together as shown.</p>\n<p><img src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\"/></p>\n<p>What is the order of increasing total capacitance for these arrangements?</p>\n<p>A.  P, S, R, Q</p>\n<p>B.  Q, R, S, P</p>\n<p>C.  P, R, S, Q</p>\n<p>D.  Q, S, R, P</p>\n</div>", "solution_html": "<div class=\"question\">\n<p>C</p>\n</div>", "examiners_html": "<div class=\"question\">\n<p>Option C was the most common selection, however all other options were effective distractors. This question would be useful in a review of combined capacitance when capacitors in series and parallel.</p>\n</div>"}